1
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:10,820
[A Talented Girl Grows Up]

2
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,990
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:14,190 --> 00:01:15,750
Mr. Wen, did you...

4
00:01:16,039 --> 00:01:18,150
cheat back then?

5
00:01:19,710 --> 00:01:20,660
It's fine you were accusing me.

6
00:01:20,660 --> 00:01:22,320
Why are you talking about him?

7
00:01:22,430 --> 00:01:25,070
Good, you've got my attention.

8
00:01:25,110 --> 00:01:26,890
I, Cheng Manyi, accept the challenge.

9
00:01:26,890 --> 00:01:27,600
No.

10
00:01:28,380 --> 00:01:30,180
Don't fall for his provocation.

11
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:30,470
Yes.

12
00:01:30,510 --> 00:01:31,550
Old Crow tried so hard

13
00:01:31,550 --> 00:01:33,140
to get me and just wouldn't let go.

14
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:35,670
Whether I face it or not, it's the same result.

15
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:36,530
Then,

16
00:01:37,140 --> 00:01:38,070
are you confident?

17
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:38,630
No.

18
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:40,700
Well...

19
00:01:41,850 --> 00:01:42,580
Don't worry.

20
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:44,670
If...

21
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,979
I won't implicate you.

22
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:52,940
Don't worry.

23
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,880
I'm not afraid of being implicated by you.

24
00:02:04,260 --> 00:02:06,060
Let me give you a question first.

25
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,630
How about composing a poem using the objects

26
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:10,139
in this courtyard as inspiration?

27
00:02:10,139 --> 00:02:12,540
Miss Cheng, please.

28
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:18,150
If you still can't do it,

29
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:20,600
I will be one step ahead.

30
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:21,910
By then,

31
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:25,550
the title of the World's Greatest Talented Woman in the world...

32
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:34,720
Goose.

33
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:39,270
Goose, Goose, Goose…

34
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,230
Goose?

35
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:42,390
Why are you laughing?

36
00:02:42,390 --> 00:02:43,600
Is it funny?

37
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:45,520
I say it's a good poem.

38
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:48,780
Is this a poem?

39
00:02:48,950 --> 00:02:51,010
Does it even deserve to be called one?

40
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,670
Huh.

41
00:02:52,730 --> 00:02:53,620
I almost forgot

42
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:54,960
the necessary skill in the time travel drama—

43
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,130
copying poems.

44
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,020
Tang poems, Song poems, and Yuan Songs.

45
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,440
I'll mix everything together.

46
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,430
It'll be enough

47
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,590
to stun you ancient people!

48
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,820
I'll destroy you.

49
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:03,890
Miss Cheng,

50
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:07,190
Is your ignorance going to be exposed?

51
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:11,390
Goose, Goose, Goose,

52
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:15,930
Sings to the sky with its neck curved.

53
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:19,110
White feathers float atop green waters.

54
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:23,550
Red feet stir up clear ripples.

55
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:25,420
That's great.

56
00:03:25,450 --> 00:03:27,010
It's a preemptive opening.

57
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:27,590
Wonderful.

58
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:28,710
The verses are meticulously balanced,

59
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:29,950
with an interplay of movement and stillness,

60
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:31,480
creating endless marvels.

61
00:03:31,490 --> 00:03:33,410
This wonderful work

62
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:34,980
does not seem impromptu.

63
00:03:35,310 --> 00:03:38,210
It's more like something you remembered beforehand.

64
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:40,210
Did she memorize it in advance?

65
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,730
Was it plagiarism?

66
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,550
Yes.

67
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:43,310
Enough.

68
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:44,840
Don't bother.

69
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:46,750
Take turns to give me questions.

70
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:47,980
I'm in a hurry.

71
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,890
I want to fight with ten at the same time!

72
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,930
When life goes well, one must revel.

73
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:08,220
Never show an empty cup to the moon.

74
00:04:09,420 --> 00:04:11,420
The bright moon shines over the sea.

75
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:14,740
From far away, we share this moment.

76
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:19,470
Don't worry about having no friends.

77
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:22,910
Who does not know you in this world?

78
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:26,030
I want to compare West Lake to a beauty.

79
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:30,190
It's equally beautiful with light or heavy makeup on.

80
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:34,140
What is love in the world?

81
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:39,940
It makes people pledge their lives to one another.

82
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:42,310
Suddenly, as if a spring breeze came overnight,

83
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:45,070
Thousands of pear trees blossom at the same time.

84
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,070
The water falls down 3,000 feet,

85
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:48,870
Like the Milky Way falls from the sky.

86
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:50,430
The moon shines in front of my bed.

87
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:52,230
I mistook it for the frost on the ground.

88
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:52,870
Can you see

89
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:54,870
The water of the Yellow River comes from the sky

90
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,390
And races to the sea without ever returning?

91
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:58,990
Heaven gave me talent for a reason.

92
00:04:58,990 --> 00:05:01,390
Spend now; riches return in season.

93
00:05:01,390 --> 00:05:02,670
I rise and dance; with my shadow, I play.

94
00:05:02,670 --> 00:05:03,710
On high as on earth, would it be as gay?

95
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:05,030
I know not in heaven's palaces

96
00:05:05,030 --> 00:05:07,030
What year it is this night.

97
00:05:07,030 --> 00:05:09,740
Sing to the wine and celebrate, for life is but a fleeting moment.

98
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:11,470
I long to ride the wind and return;

99
00:05:11,470 --> 00:05:13,310
Yet fear that marble towers and jade houses…

100
00:05:13,310 --> 00:05:16,910
A thousand times, I've been seeking him among the crowds.

101
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:18,570
And just when I turned around,

102
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,320
There he was,

103
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,620
where the lantern lights

104
00:05:42,130 --> 00:05:45,680
were dim.

105
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:49,210
A thousand times, I've been seeking him among the crowds.

106
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:51,650
And just when I turned around,

107
00:05:51,730 --> 00:05:55,240
♫The candle is burning out, the dawn is breaking♫

108
00:05:52,950 --> 00:05:57,110
There he was, where the lantern lights are dim.

109
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:58,260
♫The moon knows my thoughts♫

110
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:02,490
♫Life is so long, I hope to spend♫

111
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:05,640
♫The rest of my life with you♫

112
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:06,270
Good poem.

113
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:09,850
♫It's a long way to go♫

114
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:08,750
Such a beautiful love

115
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:10,670
is as sweet as honey.

116
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:19,590
♫May I have a lifelong partner♫

117
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:12,750
I'm shipping!

118
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:24,520
♫Let me be your lover♫

119
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:23,970
Let go of me!

120
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,400
Cui Jun.

121
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:30,890
You did it on purpose.

122
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,810
Didn't you ask me to let go?

123
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:33,940
Tell me.

124
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:35,290
He's so unromantic.

125
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:37,270
How can he let go?

126
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:43,580
Congratulations, Miss Cheng, for winning the Poetry Meeting.

127
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:46,370
According to tradition, we need you to dedicate a poem

128
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:48,760
and ask Mr. Wen to seal it.

129
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:51,670
I'll keep it and appreciate it from time to time.

130
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:52,930
Hey, old man.

131
00:06:52,970 --> 00:06:54,090
Are you done?

132
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:55,430
What do you mean?

133
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:05,820
Okay. Here, Honey.

134
00:07:13,580 --> 00:07:15,660
Miss Cheng, can't you write?

135
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,660
Why do you need Mr. Wen's help?

136
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:20,870
I'm always writing with my husband like this

137
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:22,500
when we're at home.

138
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:23,950
Am I right, Honey?

139
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:26,390
Yes. You're so naughty.

140
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:27,970
Don't you like my man?

141
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,430
Then, I'll show you how much we're in love

142
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:30,610
to piss you off.

143
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:38,960
Here, Honey.

144
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:53,080
This poem is specially written for Vice Censor-in-Chief Du.

145
00:07:53,130 --> 00:07:54,500
Please enjoy it.

146
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,700
We're leaving.

147
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,540
Thank you, Miss Cheng.

148
00:07:57,820 --> 00:07:58,880
Thank you, Mr. Wen.

149
00:08:04,590 --> 00:08:07,250
In matters of culture, I am deficient,

150
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:10,420
and my intellect is meager;

151
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:13,990
inquire of my essence,

152
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:18,400
and I am but a grand, unrefined creature.

153
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:20,490
I am a creature.

154
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:23,450
I am an unrefined creature.

155
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:26,980
I am a grand, unrefined creature.

156
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,210
Good poem.

157
00:08:31,790 --> 00:08:32,590
Father.

158
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,360
Okay, thank you.

159
00:08:40,610 --> 00:08:42,970
Old Crow will go crazy with rage.

160
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:46,820
Your performance just now

161
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:49,110
really impressed me.

162
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:50,240
Truly impressive.

163
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:52,660
Of course. Am I good?

164
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,950
But I don't understand.

165
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:58,320
You are a genius.

166
00:08:58,350 --> 00:09:00,580
Why can't you read?

167
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:05,240
That's because I...

168
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:12,470
Fine.

169
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:15,930
I admit I didn't compose those poems.

170
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,070
I just...

171
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:20,310
What's wrong?

172
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,540
Don't look around.

173
00:09:25,780 --> 00:09:26,780
I finally found you.

174
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:27,520
You...

175
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,220
We're being followed.

176
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:34,990
He...

177
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:36,480
Let's go.

178
00:09:37,370 --> 00:09:38,470
Let's go.

179
00:09:38,690 --> 00:09:39,440
This is...

180
00:09:39,730 --> 00:09:40,510
Move!

181
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:44,350
Go upstairs! Hurry!

182
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:47,020
-This way.
-Go!

183
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:48,450
Catch him!

184
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:48,980
Get him!

185
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,400
This way.

186
00:09:50,470 --> 00:09:51,660
-This way.
-This way. Hurry.

187
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:52,870
Stop!

188
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:56,850
Run! Why don't you run anymore?

189
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,060
Do you trust me?

190
00:10:15,950 --> 00:10:16,830
Stop!

191
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:17,550
Run!

192
00:10:18,930 --> 00:10:19,790
Go after them!

193
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:21,550
Excuse me.

194
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,050
Go inside.

195
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,200
Raise the sedan.

196
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:28,670
Over there!

197
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:29,200
Go!

198
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,030
Go! Go!

199
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,810
Move!

200
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,270
-Move!
-Move!

201
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:35,830
Get lost!

202
00:10:37,180 --> 00:10:37,790
Go away!

203
00:10:37,810 --> 00:10:38,460
Go away!

204
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,640
Be gentle.

205
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:46,850
Go!

206
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,390
Please spare my life.

207
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:50,300
We have never seen the buyer.

208
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:51,510
We just said

209
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,920
we'd trade in this shabby temple.

210
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,660
Payment upon delivery.

211
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,230
Really?

212
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:57,740
I'm telling the truth.

213
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,600
Manyi.

214
00:10:59,710 --> 00:11:01,780
Looks like he's telling the truth.

215
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,280
According to your analysis,

216
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:12,820
Vice Censor-in-Chief Du stirred up so much trouble today

217
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,930
just to get the seal?

218
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:15,850
A serial trap.

219
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,500
It'd be great if he could expose your identity.

220
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:22,140
If that was the case, our entire Wen family would be executed,

221
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:23,850
and we'd have to hand over the seal.

222
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:24,640
If not,

223
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,750
he also has a last move,

224
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:28,610
which is to grab the seal by force.

225
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:30,070
Old Crow is so cunning.

226
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:31,270
Manyi,

227
00:11:31,490 --> 00:11:34,200
why are we dressed like this?

228
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:37,690
Vice Censor-in-Chief Du is just a pawn.

229
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,240
Guess

230
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,540
what he would do after he got the seal.

231
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,730
He'll surely ask the mastermind for credit.

232
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:46,940
I see.

233
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:51,190
You mean we should be dressed as killers

234
00:11:51,190 --> 00:11:52,740
to follow Vice Censor-in-Chief Du

235
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:54,870
and find out the mastermind behind it.

236
00:11:59,550 --> 00:12:00,750
You're smart, Honey.

237
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:03,950
The person behind it must be a big shot.

238
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:06,750
Besides, it was such a big event today.

239
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:08,210
I think

240
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,990
they were watching our every move

241
00:12:09,990 --> 00:12:11,500
behind the scenes.

242
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:18,770
I think I saw the Crown Prince at the Poetry Meeting today.

243
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:30,240
Looks like we're going to catch a big fish.

244
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:16,590
Who are you?

245
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:19,300
Watch out!

246
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:27,030
Come with us to testify against Vice Censor-in-Chief Du.

247
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:35,690
It's a death guard.

248
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:37,630
A death guard?

249
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:41,840
We have to report it to the City Guard Department to deal with it.

250
00:13:42,810 --> 00:13:43,780
Darn it!

251
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:46,030
How did Old Crow escape?

252
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:55,500
Luckily, you

253
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,180
saw through Wen Chenyi's trap today

254
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:58,830
and informed me to leave in advance.

255
00:13:58,830 --> 00:14:00,770
Otherwise, it's not a big deal for me to be arrested.

256
00:14:00,770 --> 00:14:02,520
But it will also get you into trouble.

257
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,720
Then, I wouldn't be able to absolve myself from the blame.

258
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:10,570
Please rest assured, My Lord.

259
00:14:10,770 --> 00:14:13,860
I will find another way

260
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:14,900
to

261
00:14:14,970 --> 00:14:17,870
bring the seal back!

262
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:23,950
[A Talented Girl Grows Up]

263
00:14:24,430 --> 00:14:25,910
I thought the clue was lost

264
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,710
and it was all for nothing today.

265
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,270
I didn't expect

266
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:30,980
you to be so meticulous.

267
00:14:31,190 --> 00:14:33,810
You can even get a clue

268
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,700
from the fabric of his underwear.

269
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:38,890
Aren't you afraid?

270
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:41,790
What a joke.

271
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:43,990
I don't know what fear is.

272
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:47,820
The cloth came from the Eastern Palace.

273
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,690
The person behind it might be the Crown Prince.

274
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:52,610
If we go against the Crown Prince,

275
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,900
our future is bound to be

276
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,010
treacherous.

277
00:14:58,570 --> 00:14:59,630
Aren't you afraid?

278
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:02,390
I said I'd protect you.

279
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:06,330
I'm a heroin of my word.

280
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:11,860
Let's lure the enemy into a trap

281
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:14,130
and catch them in the trap.

282
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,600
Okay.

283
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:24,490
Anyway, I did a good job today.

284
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,710
